▶ {nuQaw'qu'be'.:sen}
▶ {noH QapmeH wo' Qaw'lu'chugh yay chavbe'lu' 'ej wo' choqmeH may' DoHlu'chugh lujbe'lu'.:sen}
▶ {not Soj QaQ Qaw' tlhInganpu'.:sen}

This literally means "little {Qa':n:1,nolink}", though a {Qa'Hom:n:nolink} is not a young {Qa':n:1,nolink}, which is a larger, more dangerous animal. However, it does bear a vague resemblance. This word is also used as an epithet to denote someone who is weak and scared easily, and whom there is no honour in killing.[2]

This animal does not make a ruckus at dawn, unlike the {jajlo' Qa':n}. It is mistaken for a bird by some.[3] 

