▶ {DopDaq qul yIchenmoH QobDI' ghu'.:sen}
▶ {Qob qo' qeylIS yIqIm:sen:nolink} "Kahless, be aware of danger in all forms."[2, p.66-67]
▶ {pa' bIQam bIHIvDI':sen:nolink}
   {QIncha' Darur qu' 'ej run:sen:nolink}
   {Qobbogh may' nI' jun:sen:nolink}
  "You stood there, you attack
   Like a krencha, short and fierce,
   Avoiding long and dangerous battle."[2, p.156-157]

This is simply the verb {Qoch:v} plus the suffix {-be':v}.[2]

{Qochbe':v:nolink} implies an absence of disagreement, whereas {QochHa':v:nolink} implies that disagreement was misplaced or undone.[3]

Agreement is also expressed by the idiomatic expression {wa' DoS wIqIp.:sen:idiom}

